&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Board Certified Assistant Behavior Analyst (BCaBA) is responsible for protocol modifications on skill programs and behavior intervention programs designed by Board Certified Behavior Analysts (BCBAs) for children with autism spectrum disorder. This role serves as the bridge between treatment plans and direct implementation, ensuring all interventions meet specified clinical standards and achieve meaningful outcomes for our clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
